.TH "remove_ima_buffer" 9 "remove_ima_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
remove_ima_buffer \- remove the IMA buffer property and reservation from @fdt
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" remove_ima_buffer
.BI "(void *fdt "  ","
.BI "int chosen_node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fdt" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "chosen_node" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The IMA measurement buffer is of no use to a subsequent kernel, so we always
remove it from the device tree.
